{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SfFvpFt8PGq4spo8RggWJJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Progress Log\n     2→\n     3→This file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\n     4→after each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n     5→\n     6→## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n     7→\n     8→- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n     9→- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n    10→- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n    11→- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n    12→- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n    13→\n    14→---\n    15→\n    16→## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n    17→- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n    18→- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n    19→- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n    20→- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n    21→- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n    22→- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n    23→- **Files changed:**\n    24→  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n    25→  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n    26→  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n    27→  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n    28→  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n    29→  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n    30→  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n    31→  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n    32→  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n    33→- **Learnings:**\n    34→  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n    35→  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n    36→  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n    37→  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n    38→  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n    39→---\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41190ff1-9bd1-4724-abab-7aeb2422d4f8","uuid":"84656d2b-4578-45b9-bad4-b62b35b5762c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","content":"# Ralph Progress Log\n\nThis file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\nafter each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n\n## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}}
